    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/st-davids-lamb-leek-and-carrot-cawl-style-stew-with-bread-and-cheese/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> diced lamb </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until nicely browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/st-davids-lamb-leek-and-carrot-cawl-style-stew-with-bread-and-cheese/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> roughly</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and chop into large chunks</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/st-davids-lamb-leek-and-carrot-cawl-style-stew-with-bread-and-cheese/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the lamb has browned, add the <strong>garlic cloves</strong>, <strong>chopped carrot</strong>, <strong>leek</strong> and <strong>potatoes</strong> to the dish</p><p>Season with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/st-davids-lamb-leek-and-carrot-cawl-style-stew-with-bread-and-cheese/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong>, <strong>dried thyme</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>to the dish and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 500ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [650ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[850ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with the <strong>Marmite </strong>and <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, stir it all together and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, put the dish in the oven and cook, covered for 45 min or until the lamb is tender \u2013 this is your<strong> lamb, leek & carrot Welsh cawl-style stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/st-davids-lamb-leek-and-carrot-cawl-style-stew-with-bread-and-cheese/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/st-davids-lamb-leek-and-carrot-cawl-style-stew-with-bread-and-cheese/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When the stew is nearly ready, put your<strong> ciabatta[s]</strong> in the oven for 5 min or until they're hot and crusty</p><p>Carefully tear in half before serving</p><p>Roughly chop or crumble the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/st-davids-lamb-leek-and-carrot-cawl-style-stew-with-bread-and-cheese/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> lamb, leek & carrot Welsh cawl-style stew </strong>in a bowl with the <strong>crumbled cheddar </strong>over the top and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the<strong> ciabatta halves</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
